{
  "texts": [
    "The contextualized word embeddings of each token is used as token-level representation, and the fixed representation is used as the entire essay representation.",
    "These two types of information are concatenated and fed into a dense regression model to predict a score corresponding to the token-and document-level of the essay representation.",
    "To overcome the token-length constraint in BERT, this study introduces segment-level essay representation.",
    "This is accomplished by dividing essays into segments of equal token length and applying independent BERT models to each segment.",
    "By utilizing LSTM and subsequent attention pooling on the fixed representations of these segments, a sequential contextual information is modeled, which is utilized for score prediction after employing a fully connected neural network."
  ]
}